verbose_text: To better characterize the inflammatory responses in these mice, we quantified the plasma levels of cytokines (TNF-alpha, IL-6, and IL-18) and chemokines (CCL2, CXCL1, and CXCL2) that have been previously identified to contribute to different pathogenic responses in atherosclerosis and hepatic inflammation.
evidence: levels of cytokines (TNF-alpha, IL-6, and IL-18) and chemokines
